==English==

===Noun===
'''Thought Police''' ''collective noun''

#From George Orwell's 1984. A Gestapo organization responsible for monitoring all citizens and making sure they are not guilty of political dissent, or thoughtcrime.
#A wiki sysop who alters or deletes words and their definitions and blocks access of contributors who post them. 

====Examples====
Wiktionary sysops are on their way to becoming Thought Police.
My mother would make a good Though Police.

====Usage note====
*Formerly a singular [[noun phrase]], '''Thought Police''' is now almost always used as a collective noun phrase with a plural verb, as in "Run, the Though Police are coming!"

